==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evensong
<hw>E"ven*song`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦aemac⟧fensang</ets>.]</ety> <def>A song for the evening; the
evening service or form of worship (in the Church of England including
vespers and compline); also, the time of evensong.</def> <rj><au>Wyclif.
Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

